  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a random variable. Then the following are equivalent.
  <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is sub-Gaussian;</html:li>
    <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\exists  a > 0]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {E}(\exp (aX^2)) < \infty ]]></fr:tex>;</html:li>
    <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\exists  \ell ]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  \lambda  > 0]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {E}(\exp (\lambda  X)) \leq  X \exp (\lambda ^2 \ell )]]></fr:tex>;</html:li>
    <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\exists  K' > 0]]></fr:tex> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  p > 1]]></fr:tex> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathbb {E}|X|^{p})^{1/p} \leq  K' \sqrt {p}]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol></html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
